fields.name: deviceMask
fields.description: Mask which selects the memory devices for saving and/or clearing operation. Note that if a deviceMask is not provided, the receiver defaults the operation requested to battery-backed RAM (BBR) and Flash (if available). This field is only present if the payload length is 13 bytes.

structure.name: UBX-CFG-CFG
structure.description: Used to configure the receiver and poll current configuration values, as well as for sending commands to the receiver. Unless stated otherwise, any message in this class sent to the receiver is either acknowledged (by a UBX-ACK-ACK message) if processed successfully or rejected (with a UBX-ACK-NAK message) if processed unsuccessfully. This message can clear, save, and load configurations.

variable.description: Payload is 12 bytes if deviceMask is omitted, 13 bytes if deviceMask is included (optional group).

fields.name: clearMask
fields.description: Mask for configuration to clear. If any bit is set, all saved configuration from the selected non-volatile memory is cleared.

fields.name: saveMask
fields.description: Mask for configuration to save. If any bit is set, all current configuration is stored to the selected layers.

fields.name: loadMask
fields.description: Mask for configuration to load. If any bit is set, current configuration is discarded and rebuilt from lower non-volatile memory layers.

fields.name: deviceMask
fields.description: Mask which selects the memory devices for saving and/or clearing operation. Note that if a deviceMask is not provided, the receiver defaults the operation requested to battery-backed RAM (BBR) and Flash (if available). This field is optional.

bits.name: devEEPROM
bits.description: EEPROM (only supported for protocol versions less than 14.00)

bits.name: devSpiFlash
bits.description: SPI Flash (only supported for protocol versions less than 14.00)

structure.name: UBX-CFG-CFG
structure.description: Clear, save and load configurations for the receiver. This message's behavior changed for protocol versions greater than 23.01; newer versions should use UBX-CFG-VALSET and UBX-CFG-VALDEL. It allows clearing, saving, and loading configuration based on masks, with commands combinable. Execution sequence is clear, save, then load.

fields.name: clearMask
fields.description: Mask with configuration sub-sections to clear (i.e. load default configurations to permanent configurations in non-volatile memory)

fields.name: saveMask
fields.description: Mask with configuration sub-sections to save (i.e. save current configurations to non-volatile memory), see ID description of clearMask

fields.name: loadMask
fields.description: Mask with configuration sub-sections to load (i.e. load permanent configurations from non-volatile memory to current configurations), see ID description of clearMask

fields.name: deviceMask
fields.description: Mask which selects the memory devices for this command.
